A teacher has been suspended after reportedly throwing a bucket of water on a couple of teens he caught kissing and hugging in a school corridor.

The unnamed teacher was placed on administrative leave while officials look into the incident at a Nashville High School.

But he appeared unrepentant about his actions in a Facebook posting saying his actions 'seemed to work' and caused the couple to break off their affectionate embrace.

